<meta name="specificfeeds-verification-code-cWV0V1J6c1BqTmNpakpoUDVMczRNYW91d3ZGMzhGemlMUUgySU5RaEJoM0I0aGNpdmpNc2pINjJlU0lBOTRRZk5Tc1VFcmRxK084L2pmWVZGY0xaU3lNZUM0QXJxaXhBbzh0WXUvNUJpcVNvVFd5ZGg0NU5EcC95aEJVQ0tVS0J8RWI3cFlaNDNYb0JEb1hwSy95UjRtbzZrWE9CdlZyOStUa1dscU9raUNaUT0=" content="N22B9fkCKVz2FTUUXmxw"/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"><meta property="og:image" content="http://coderdojoerode.space/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Dojo.jpg" data-id="sfsi"><meta property="og:image:type" content="" data-id="sfsi" /><meta property="og:image:width" content="960" data-id="sfsi" /><meta property="og:image:height" content="500" data-id="sfsi" /><meta property="og:url" content="http://coderdojoerode.space/about-us/" data-id="sfsi" /><meta property="og:description" content="How Everything Started - Arise of Coderdojo Erode




Hello,First of, thank you so much for your time and interest to know more about us. Here is our story of how we get started. Erode is a district in the state of Tamilnadu located in southern part of India.





Some of you might wonder, how CoderDojo efforts reach such a place! Answer is, this blogpost.  Go on reading!!!

In the first week of march 2015, in a fine sunday evening, few friends of  same age group (21 - 24 years old) met at a temple ground of a village called Sullipalayam located in the district Erode. It is usual they meet every week at the same place throughout the year but that evening turned out to be something special.




It is because they were making fun of a person's ignorance with ATM Debit Card. For convenience, we are naming the person with ignorance as Sasi (whose education is only to the age of 14) and other guy from the group as Tharun. Here is the conversation between the two on previous afternoon.




Sasi      : Hi Tharun, I need your help

Tharun : What is it about ? Tell me

Sasi      : I received a call few days back saying I won a jackpot. I was requested to send my personal and bank details over e-mail.

Tharun : Oh, I see. What can I help you with ?

Sasi      : It's been more than 10 days I haven't received any prize. Can you check ?

Tharun : Sure! Can I see the e-mail you have sent. Is it gmail or something else ?

Sasi      :  Gmail only. Here are the details ( he took out his Debit card while he was telling the PIN number )

Tharun : What ? Tell me your e-mail id.

Sasi      : No, I don't have one. I sent the mail from Internet cafe from my friends mail account

Tharun : Oh..ok. What did you send ?

Sasi      : They asked for my name, Date of birth, ID card number, Bank account number along with Debit card number with PIN and last 3 transaction details

Tharun : OMG! You have given the secret details to someone that you are not suppose to. They can easily take your money from the account with this.

Sasi      : Haha! why are you trying to cheat me. My card is here and how can money be taken without the card.

Tharun : Wait Wait! Money can be taken through net banking or some purchase can be made online with your money.

Sasi      : Tharun. Don't play with me. Are you serious ? What can I do now ?

Tharun : I am serious. You should be happy that no money is lost till now. Immediately change your PIN.

Sasi      : Oh okay. But, my bank is not in our city I need to travel.

Tharun : No, you can do it from ATM.

Sasi      : Yeah..there is one ATM nearby. But, I have taken a FANCY NUMBER as my PIN - 7868. If I change, someone else will take that FANCY PIN, right ?

Tharun : Ha ha ha (he blasted with laugh). No PIN number is not unique multiple persons can have same number. Only card number will be unique.





Coming back to the Sunday meeting group. On hearing the funny conversation, everyone blasted out laughing but at the same time they started thinking - Why Sasi is ignorant?. Sasi and rest of the group had their education together up to the age of 10. But, Sasi now stands too far from rest of the group in terms of technology and web literacy.

While the group decided to discuss and identify  the grass roots of the problem another guy from the group shared an another interesting story. He said that, a friend of his who also stopped education early like sasi use to pay 20 INR every time to the bank assistant for filling the deposit/withdraw form.

Group gave a much deeper thought and came to a conclusion that not all methods of education is sufficient in todays world. Only having education from books alone won't be good enough. They felt, Awareness about technology, Internet is very important for everyone no matter who they are, what they do in today's era.



While everyone agree about the issues with formal and traditional educational system but they knew well they can't change anything in a system that is in practice for so long. Instead of trying to change the system, why not create a parallel option for people to obtain skills out of their interest that are currently missing. While, this sounds good but the group isn't sure how and where to start.




It is when a guy from the group shared about his understanding on CoderDojo Initiative by CoderDojo Foundation.  CoderDojo seems to be a great platform for the group to offer an opportunity for everyone to learn about technology.


We already started our activities and you can follow the same in our facebook and twitter accounts.

Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/coderdojoerode

Twitter - https://twitter.com/coderdojoerode


If you are interested in being a part of our Dojo or want to help us, you can write to erode.in@coderdojo.com

